Places.title: ReverseGeocode API Playground
Places.description: The Reverse Geocoding API transforms geographic coordinates (latitude/longitude) into detailed human-readable addresses and location information. When making a request, you'll use the QueryPosition parameter which requires a latitude/longitude pair like '47.6174, -122.3375'. The API accepts several optional parameters to refine results: BiasPosition lets you prioritize results near specific coordinates, Filter allows you to restrict results to certain countries or boundary areas, and MaxResults controls the number of returned locations (1-100). The API returns a JSON response containing ResultItems, each with detailed address components (street address, city, state, country), the exact position coordinates, and any additional requested data. For enhanced results, you can use AdditionalFeatures to request supplementary information like time zones. Query customization helps ensure relevant results — for example, using Filter with specific countries can help ensure addresses are returned from your desired region rather than similar coordinates worldwide.

codeSnippets.Python:
import boto3

# Initialize the client
client = boto3.client('geo-places', region_name='us-east-1')  # Replace with your region

# Create the reverse geocode request
params = {
    'QueryPosition': [{{queryPosition}}],  # [longitude, latitude]
}

# Make the request
response = client.reverse_geocode(**params)
print(response)

Places.title: Geocode API Playground
Places.description: The Geocoding API transforms addresses or place names into geographic coordinates with detailed location information. When building a query, you have two main approaches: use the [[Query]] parameter for simple free-form text input like "123 Main St, Boston, MA", or use [[QueryComponents]] for precise structured queries where address elements (street, city, country) are specified separately. The API accepts several optional parameters to refine results: [[BiasPosition]] lets you provide coordinates to prioritize results near a specific location, [[Filter]] allows you to restrict results to certain countries or place types, [[Language]] determines the response language, and [[AdditionalFeatures]] allows you to restrict results to certain countries or place types, can request extra data such as time zones. The API returns a JSON response containing coordinates, formatted address components, and any additional requested information. Query customization helps ensure accurate results — for example, combining [[BiasPosition]] with [[Filter]] can help find the correct "Main Street" in a specific city rather than returning matches from around the world.

Places.title: Search Nearby API Playground
Places.description: The Search Nearby API finds places within a specified radius from a given origin point. Use [[Origin]] with latitude/longitude coordinates and [[Radius]] to define the search area. Select [[Categories]] to filter results by place type. Optional parameters include [[BoundingBox]], [[ExcludeBusinessChains]], [[ExcludeCategories]], [[ExcludeFoodTypes]], [[IncludeBusinessChains]], [[IncludeCategories]], [[IncludeFoodTypes]], [[IncludeCountries]], [[IntendedUse]], [[Language]], [[MaxResults]], [[PoliticalView]], and [[QueryRadius]] for advanced filtering.
